From: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Mon, 15 Dec 2025 10:11:45 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] phy: intel-lgm-emmc: Be tolerant to card clock of 0 in power
 on

It's possible that there are some reasons to turn the PHY on while the
clock is 0. In this case we just won't wait for the DLL to lock.

phy-intel-keembay-emmc and phy-rockchip-emmc drivers do the same.

Note: this patch should help with suspend/resume where the system will
try to turn the PHY back on when the clock is 0.

Fixes: 922794238330 ("phy: intel-lgm-emmc: Add support for eMMC PHY")
Signed-off-by: Martin Schiller <ms@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c | 20 +++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c b/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c
index d6c26a902d10..28680ef90eae 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-emmc.c
@@ -68,6 +68,13 @@ static int intel_emmc_phy_power(struct phy *phy, bool on_off)
 		return ret;
 	}
 
+	ret = regmap_update_bits(priv->syscfg, EMMC_PHYCTRL1_REG, ENDLL_MASK,
+				 ENDLL_SHIFT(0));
+	if (ret) {
+		dev_err(&phy->dev, "turn off the dll failed: %d\n", ret);
+		return ret;
+	}
+
 	/* Already finish power_off above */
 	if (!on_off)
 		return 0;
@@ -77,7 +84,6 @@ static int intel_emmc_phy_power(struct phy *phy, bool on_off)
 	if (quot > 4)
 		dev_warn(&phy->dev, "Unsupported rate: %lu\n", rate);
 	switch (quot) {
-	case 0:
 	case 1:
 		freqsel = FRQSEL_50M;
 		break;
@@ -137,6 +143,18 @@ static int intel_emmc_phy_power(struct phy *phy, bool on_off)
 		return ret;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * We turned on the DLL even though the rate was 0 because we the
+	 * clock might be turned on later.  ...but we can't wait for the DLL
+	 * to lock when the rate is 0 because it will never lock with no
+	 * input clock.
+	 *
+	 * Technically we should be checking the lock later when the clock
+	 * is turned on, but for now we won't.
+	 */
+	if (rate == 0)
+		return 0;
+
 	/*
 	 * After enabling analog DLL circuits docs say that we need 10.2 us if
 	 * our source clock is at 50 MHz and that lock time scales linearly
